trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection> allows to centralize the management of the output cache settings used by pages or user controls.
It allows you to programmatically access and modify the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile> objects it contains.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile> can be applied to a page using the `CacheProfile` attribute of the [@ OutputCache](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/28a9e101-fb44-4198-9cb6-b8a52312fec2) directive.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> class.
Adds a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object to the collection.
The collection cannot contain a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile> object with the same name.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object to add to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object already exists in the collection or the collection is read only.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> keys.
The `string` array containing the collection keys.
Removes all the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> objects from the collection.
This method inserts a `clear` directive into the corresponding section of the configuration file to clear all references to elements defined in a higher-level configuration file.
All elements defined in the corresponding section of the current configuration file are removed.
The collection is read only.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element at the specified index.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> element.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element at the specified index.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element with the specified name.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> element.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element with the specified name.
Gets the key at the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> index.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> index of the key.
The key with the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> index.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object at the specified index.
The collection index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> at the specified index.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> with the specified name.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> with the specified name.
Removes the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object with the specified name from the collection.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection.Remove%2A> method inserts a `remove` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element to remove from the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object with the specified key in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Removes the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object at the specified index from the collection.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection.RemoveAt%2A> method inserts a `remove` element into the corresponding section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the corresponding section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The index of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> element to remove from the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object with the specified key in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Sets the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfile"></xref> object.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection.Set%2A> method modifies an existing <xref:System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection> element.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> element to set.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.OutputCacheProfileCollection"></xref> is read-only.
